The paper deals with stochastic optimization of cloud radio access networks (C-RANs) by joint remote radio head (RRH) activation and beamforming in the downlink. This involves the use of techniques from information theory (cs.IT) to optimize the transmission of data over the network, as well as network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system engineering (cs.SY) to design and implement the C-RAN. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning (cs.MM) and optimization (cs.LG) techniques to solve the optimization problem. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT, cs.NI, and cs.SY, followed by cs.MM and cs.LG.
